column4: I'm trying to add the medibuntu repo to install googleearth, but although the repo seems to be recognized by synaptic the googleearth package does not seem to appear
Are you sure that package is in that repo?
http://packages.medibuntu.org/jaunty/index.html suggest it is
It does appear to be that way.  Are those other packages showing up?
no, none of them show up
Did you reload synaptic?  Does it show up in the origins section?
yes, medibuntu is in the list
Did you "reload" ??
yes, a dozen times
pretty weird huh?
Yes it is very odd.  Does your synaptic reload with no problems?  How did you add the repo?
yes, it reloads fine. I followed the instructions at "https://help.ubuntu.com/community/Medibuntu#Adding the Repositories" to add the key and list the repo in sources.list.d
Go into System -> Admin -> Software sources.  What checkboxes do you have enabled?
Medibuntu (non-source variant) is enabled under third-party
enabling their source variant did not help
hmm, it seems the quick search does not really search all repos when all is selected...
quick search searches what is listed in the window at that time
I hate qucik search ;)  It's counter-intuitive
when I cleared the search box I saw googleearth in the list, but when quicksearching for it only the main googleearthpackage thingy...
thanks a lot of helping me :)
NP!
